(2377, 606, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"733f90c0\",\"elType\":\"container\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"54d5afa8\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<p>The Socio-Economic Program of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) is implemented to support and enhance the economic participation,<br \\/>productivity, and overall well-being of Muslim communities. It seeks to advance inclusive and culturally responsive economic development through two<br \\/>major areas of intervention:<\\/p>\\n<!-- \\/wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list {\\\"ordered\\\":true} -->\\n<ol class=\\\"wp-block-list\\\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\\n<li>The promotion and development of Muslim Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs), including the implementation of livelihood programs and the<br \\/>support, promotion, and development of Muslim cooperatives as instruments of community-based economic growth; and<\\/li>\\n<!-- \\/wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item -->\\n<li>The promotion and development of the Halal industry, which covers Halal advocacy, technical and capacity-building initiatives, and efforts related<br \\/>to Islamic banking and finance to expand access to Shari\\u2019ah-compliant economic opportunities.<br \\/>These interventions are aligned with the Commission\\u2019s mandate to advance the socio-economic welfare and sustainable development of Muslim Filipinos.<br \\/>*Pics of activities (TO FOLLOW)<\\/li>\\n<!-- \\/wp:list-item --><\\/ol>\\n<!-- \\/wp:list -->\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
