(2480, 327, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"1e7ba7e6\",\"elType\":\"container\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"22807020\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\\n<h1><strong>NCMF Regional Office IX<\\/strong> \\u2013 <em>Zamboanga Peninsula<\\/em><\\/h1>\\n<p>\\u00a0<\\/p>\\n<p>The National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (<strong>NCMF<\\/strong>) Regional Office IX serves the Muslim communities of the Zamboanga Peninsula, covering Zamboanga<br \\/>City, Zamboanga del Sur, Zamboanga del Norte, and Zamboanga Sibugay. Guided by Republic Act 9997, the office implements NCMF\\u2019s policies, programs,<br \\/>and services to promote the welfare, rights, and development of Muslim Filipinos in the region.<\\/p>\\n<h2><br \\/>Mandate<\\/h2>\\n<p>Preserve and develop the culture, tradition, institutions and well-being of Muslim Filipinos, in conformity with the country\'s laws and in consonance with<br \\/>national unity and development.<\\/p>\\n<p><br \\/>NCMF Regional Office IX is mandated to carry out the Commission\\u2019s core functions in the region, including socio-economic development, cultural<br \\/>preservation, Muslim civil registry support, legal assistance, Hajj operations, and peace-building efforts. The office ensures that national programs are<br \\/>effectively delivered to local communities and that Muslim Filipinos have access to services that promote inclusivity and empowerment.<\\/p>\\n<!-- \\/wp:paragraph -->\",\"text_color\":\"#1A1A1A\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
