(2912, 710, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"5ef6ff2\",\"elType\":\"container\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5448e81\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<h1><strong>Office of the Regional Director<\\/strong><\\/h1><div><strong>\\u00a0<\\/strong><\\/div><p><strong>The Office of the Regional Director<\\/strong> provides overarching leadership, policy direction, and administrative supervision to the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) Regional Office IX \\u2013 Zamboanga Peninsula. As the highest executive office within the regional structure, it ensures the faithful implementation of the Commission\\u2019s mandate pursuant to Republic Act No. 9997, and upholds the principles of public service, accountability, and cultural integrity in all regional operations.<\\/p><p>The Regional Director exercises authority over all divisions and units within the regional office, ensuring the efficient and coordinated delivery of programs and services related to socio-economic development, cultural preservation, Muslim civil registry support, legal affairs, Halal industry development, peace building and conflict resolution, and the facilitation of Hajj affairs. The office likewise oversees the formulation of regional plans, the monitoring and evaluation of program performance, and the alignment of regional initiatives with national priorities.<\\/p><p>Moreover, the Office of the Regional Director represents the Commission in all official engagements within the Zamboanga Peninsula, fosters strong interagency collaboration, and sustains partnerships with local government units, national government agencies, Muslim religious leaders, civil society<br \\/>organizations, and community stakeholders. Through strategic governance and principled leadership, the office remains committed to advancing the welfare, rights, and holistic development of Muslim Filipinos in the region.<\\/p><p><!-- \\/wp:paragraph --><\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#1A1A1A\"},\"elements\"