(3090, 734, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"8f5cbf4\",\"elType\":\"container\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"5f63327\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<h1>SOCIO-ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT DIVISION (SEDD)<\\/h1><div><br><\\/div><div><br><\\/div>\\n<p>The Socio-Economic Development Division (SEDD) of NCMF Regional Office IX A \\u2013 Zamboanga Peninsula is dedicated to empowering Muslim communities across the region through sustainable livelihood development, skills enhancement, and socio-economic upliftment programs. The division leads the implementation of projects that promote economic self-reliance, access to opportunities, and inclusive growth for Muslim Filipinos.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\\n<p>SEDD supports the development, promotion, and protection of the Halal industry by ensuring that community-based economic programs align with Halal principles and standards. It likewise leads the implementation of Halal-related socio-economic initiatives in the region, including capability-building sessions, <br>awareness activities, and support to Halal-compliant enterprises and livelihood programs. The division also works closely with Halal Certifying Bodies, national government agencies, local government units, cooperatives, and Muslim organizations to strengthen the Halal ecosystem and expand market opportunities for Muslim Filipinos.<\\/p>\\n<p>Guided by the mandate of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos, SEDD IXA continues to champion programs that improve quality of life, strengthen <br>local economies, and uphold the welfare and dignity of Muslim communities in Zamboanga Peninsula.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#1A1A1A\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
