(3184, 747, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"9b578a3\",\"elType\":\"container\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"bf9c970\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<h1>PEACE BUILDING AND CONFLICT RESOLUTION DIVISION (PBCRD)<\\/h1><div><br><\\/div><div><br><\\/div>\\n<p><\\/p>\\n<p>The Peace Building and Conflict Resolution Division (PBCRD) of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos Regional Office IX serves as the primary institutional mechanism for advancing the Commission\\u2019s mandate on fostering durable peace, social order, and harmonious relations within and among Muslim communities in the Zamboanga Peninsula. Guided by the national policy framework on peace, security, and development, the Division undertakes strategic interventions designed to prevent, mitigate, and resolve conflicts through culturally sensitive, rights-based, and community-centered approaches.<\\/p>\\n<p><\\/p>\\n<p>The PBCRD exercises its function through the formulation and implementation of peace education initiatives, mediation and dialogue platforms, community engagement programs, and coordinated actions with national government agencies, local government units, civil society organizations, and traditional and <br>religious leaders. These undertakings aim to strengthen institutional capacities for conflict resolution, safeguard the welfare of Muslim Filipinos, and cultivate an environment conducive to mutual respect, inclusive governance, and sustainable peace.<\\/p>\",\"text_color\":\"#1A1A1A\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
