(96, 1, '2025-11-07 11:48:52', '2025-11-07 11:48:52', '<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/banner-1024x395.jpg\" alt=\"The current image has no alternative text. The file name is: banner-scaled.jpg\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column {\"width\":\"100%\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\" style=\"flex-basis:100%\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>         </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Zamboanga City  The National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) <a></a>Regional Office for Zamboanga Peninsula held its first official management meeting on July 28, 2025, marking a pivotal moment under the fresh leadership of the newly designated Regional Director, Dir. Rhoaisa S. Matolo-Mukaram.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The meeting brought together Provincial Heads from various provinces across the region, along with Division Chiefs of the regional office, for a comprehensive briefing and consultative session. The purpose: to establish alignment, build synergy, and discuss the Commissions direction under Director Matolo-Mukarams leadership.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During the session, the Regional Director was thoroughly appraised of each division and provincial offices key functions, notable accomplishments, strategic plans, and existing challenges. The presentations highlighted the resilience and dedication of the NCMF teams, especially in implementing programs and services despite limited resources.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Director Matolo-Mukaram, in her remarks, expressed deep appreciation for the work already undertaken and emphasized her commitment to a collaborative, transparent, and impact-driven approach to public service.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is more than a meetingit is a renewed commitment to the Muslim Filipino communities we serve. As we move forward, I believe in inclusive leadership and empowering our frontliners to shape a more responsive NCMF, she stated.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Participants also candidly raised concerns and suggestions during the open forum, fostering a healthy exchange of ideas and reaffirming the culture of trust and teamwork within the regional leadership.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The event concluded on a high note with shared optimism and a unified goal of improving the welfare, rights, and recognition of Muslim Filipinos in the Zamboanga Peninsula.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Regional Director\'s Corner', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'regional-director', '', '', '2025-11-10 09:00:11', '2025-11-10 09:00:11', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?page_id=96', 0, 'page', '', 0),
