(303, 1, '2025-11-10 11:21:23', '2025-11-10 11:21:23', '<!-- wp:image -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/574319940_122128977302967033_2850075004487788886_n-768x1024.jpg\" alt=\"The current image has no alternative text. The file name is: 574319940_122128977302967033_2850075004487788886_n.jpg\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a deeply spiritual moment of reflection <a></a>and gratitude, Regional Director Rhoaisa S. Matolo-Mukaram, JD, together with her team from the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) Regional Office IX-A Zamboanga Peninsula, visited the Sheikh Karimul Makdum Mosque in Barangay Tubig Indangan, Simunul, Tawi-Tawi  the first mosque ever built in the Philippines  in commemoration of its 645th founding anniversary.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Standing before the sacred structure that marks the dawn of Islam in our land, RD Matolo-Mukaram paid heartfelt tribute to the legacy of Sheikh Karimul Makdum (Rahimahullah), whose arrival in the 14th century brought the light of Islam to the shores of Tawi-Tawi and the hearts of the Bangsamoro people.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The visit was more than ceremonial  it was a pilgrimage of faith and identity, a humble reminder that before the flags and politics, before the boundaries and divisions, there was Islam  a faith that united hearts under the banner of peace, mercy, and surrender to Allah (SWT).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>RD Matolo-Mukaram shared that the story of Sheikh Makdum is not just history; it is a living testimony of dawah, perseverance, and transformation. From this very soil, the message of   ,   first echoed, shaping the spiritual destiny of the Filipino Muslims for more than six centuries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Today, as the Muslim world faces new challenges of faith, unity, and modernity, this sacred mosque stands as a symbol of resilience and renewal  reminding every believer that Islam in the Philippines was not imported through conquest, but through wisdom, sincerity, and peace.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>May we continue to honor this heritage by living as ambassadors of faith, promoting understanding and compassion across all communities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> ,  ,               .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> .  . -, </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Regional Director, NCMF IX Zamboanga</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/ncmfzamboangapeninsula?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZXqVwvr-QhfU5bjEW4iuN11mN9KHPmEg4FJSl6GssC3J9dwUh8MLDjYKbL3PuZTfX7PZpKAV3QW-JA8uIJhQDf2whEWxsb3xXgjUxtlKIfl9AGro6jr-S89cBzNmtlBffaWqFuGnTRNnK2crjikMHcx0hli0V0k9Gsc7Px0ecaBjbnJld0A8NTF3un9qlqAeatmA0RGOdUBXSAqvY92B-T6&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\">#NCMFZamboangaPeninsula</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/newleadershipinaction?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZXqVwvr-QhfU5bjEW4iuN11mN9KHPmEg4FJSl6GssC3J9dwUh8MLDjYKbL3PuZTfX7PZpKAV3QW-JA8uIJhQDf2whEWxsb3xXgjUxtlKIfl9AGro6jr-S89cBzNmtlBffaWqFuGnTRNnK2crjikMHcx0hli0V0k9Gsc7Px0ecaBjbnJld0A8NTF3un9qlqAeatmA0RGOdUBXSAqvY92B-T6&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\">#NewLeadershipInAction</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/trabahokoibadahko?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZXqVwvr-QhfU5bjEW4iuN11mN9KHPmEg4FJSl6GssC3J9dwUh8MLDjYKbL3PuZTfX7PZpKAV3QW-JA8uIJhQDf2whEWxsb3xXgjUxtlKIfl9AGro6jr-S89cBzNmtlBffaWqFuGnTRNnK2crjikMHcx0hli0V0k9Gsc7Px0ecaBjbnJld0A8NTF3un9qlqAeatmA0RGOdUBXSAqvY92B-T6&amp;__tn__=*NK-R\">#TrabahoKoIbadahKo</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/publicservicewithaheart