(401, 1, '2025-11-14 09:58:18', '2025-11-14 09:58:18', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":404,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/wp-content/uploads/2025/11/581847885_122130363866967033_3947552022615334795_n.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-404\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>      <a></a>   .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) Region IX actively took part in the CY 2025 4th Quarter Meeting of the Regional Development Council (RDC) IX, held at Kalikasan Hall, DEPDev IX Building, Regional Government Center, Balintawak, Pagadian City on November 11, 2025.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Represented by Regional Director Atty. Rhoaisa S. Matolo-Mukaram, JD, the NCMF joined fellow regional directors and agency heads in discussing programs that shape the regions inclusive growth and sustainable future.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Out of 44 council members, 17 agencies were in attendanceincluding TESDA, DepEd, DOLE, DSWD, CPD, and several State Universities and Colleges such as Basilan State College, Western Mindanao State University, J.H. Cerilles State College, Zamboanga Peninsula Polytechnic State University, and Zamboanga State College of Marine Sciences and Technology.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Presided by Chairperson Nestor R. Carbonera, the meeting focused on reviewing and endorsing development plans that align with the regions long-term vision.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>    </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Regional Social Development Committee (RSDC IX) is the social development arm of RDC IX that ensures national policies are translated into responsive regional actionscovering social protection, education, health, culture, poverty reduction, and peacebuilding.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For the Muslim Filipinos in the Zamboanga Peninsula, this platform is crucial: it        ,            ,        with other agencies and State Universities.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is why RD Matolo-Mukaram has been consistently and actively participating in every RSDC meeting   ,   ,         ,  ,  -      - .</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During the session, RD Matolo-Mukaram emphasized the importance of the Halal Ecosystem and Peacebuilding Initiatives, responding to issues raised in the Basilan State College presentationrecommendations that will be referred to the BSC President for integration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She also presented the NCMF Development Plan 20252028 and the Regional Development Investment Plan (RDIP) for 20272028, anchored on three transformative pillars:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Socio-Protection</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Socio-Cultural Enrichment</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Socio-Economic Empowerment</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The proposal earned commendation and support from the Council.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Alhamdulillah, the meeting concluded with renewed unity and optimismaffirming that true development is achieved when faith, wisdom, and cooperation guide every action. The outcomes will be further deliberated during the RDC IX Plenary Session on December 3, 2025.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/ncmfzamboangapeninsula?__eep__=6&amp;__cft__[0]=AZW__dMo-5DYmnPB9vRa4yWt7wZqbx7_ZjL2nAgC1ApYjkXgOnhD93ICMXTk774qXuatJZGiXOcpVneV_Cagkde2MVFIM197CxEbZ6UJBW0-RqsBF9M20QGqioKVkoBa2fNUKBS3BIdFeOFTCOl6q-jFgLsI215LoxDgv_pCgCGYtN0wjry6LKOj6zWOzxSm-3ORBf