(542, 1, '2026-01-06 05:18:15', '2026-01-06 05:18:15', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Socio-Economic Program of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) is implemented to support and enhance the economic participation,<br />productivity, and overall well-being of Muslim communities. It seeks to advance inclusive and culturally responsive economic development through two<br />major areas of intervention:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The promotion and development of Muslim Micro and Small Enterprises (MSEs), including the implementation of livelihood programs and the<br />support, promotion, and development of Muslim cooperatives as instruments of community-based economic growth; and</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>The promotion and development of the Halal industry, which covers Halal advocacy, technical and capacity-building initiatives, and efforts related<br />to Islamic banking and finance to expand access to Shariah-compliant economic opportunities.<br />These interventions are aligned with the Commissions mandate to advance the socio-economic welfare and sustainable development of Muslim Filipinos.<br />*Pics of activities (TO FOLLOW)</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->', 'Socio Economic', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'socio-economic', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:08:28', '2026-01-06 06:08:28', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?page_id=542', 0, 'page', '', 0),
