(618, 1, '2026-01-06 06:11:45', '2026-01-06 06:11:45', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) Regional Office IX serves the Muslim communities of the Zamboanga Peninsula, covering Zamboanga<br>City, Zamboanga del Sur, Zamboanga del Norte, and Zamboanga Sibugay. Guided by Republic Act 9997, the office implements NCMFs policies, programs,<br>and services to promote the welfare, rights, and development of Muslim Filipinos in the region.<br>Mandate<br>Preserve and develop the culture, tradition, institutions and well-being of Muslim Filipinos, in conformity with the country\'s laws and in consonance with<br>national unity and development.<br>NCMF Regional Office IX is mandated to carry out the Commissions core functions in the region, including socio-economic development, cultural<br>preservation, Muslim civil registry support, legal assistance, Hajj operations, and peace-building efforts. The office ensures that national programs are<br>effectively delivered to local communities and that Muslim Filipinos have access to services that promote inclusivity and empowerment.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Profile', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '327-revision-v1', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:11:45', '2026-01-06 06:11:45', '', 327, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?p=618', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
