(668, 1, '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '<h1>ADMIN AND FINANCE DIVISION (AFD)</h1><p></p><p>The Administrative and Finance Division (AFD) of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) Regional Office IX  Zamboanga Peninsula serves as <br />the principal unit responsible for the comprehensive management of administrative and financial affairs of the regional office. The division is entrusted with ensuring the efficient, transparent, and accountable administration of resources, personnel, and logistical operations in accordance with existing laws, rules, and regulations, including government auditing standards and financial management protocols.</p><p></p><p>The divisions functions encompass the preparation, allocation, and monitoring of the regional offices budget; management of disbursements and financial records; oversight of procurement, property, and inventory management; and provision of general administrative support to all divisions and units within the regional office. Through these responsibilities, the AFD guarantees that programs, projects, and activities of the regional office are operationally feasible, financially sound, and aligned with the strategic objectives of the Commission.</p>', 'Admin and Finance Division (AFD)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'admin-and-finance-division-afd', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:48:58', '2026-01-06 06:48:58', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?page_id=668', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(669, 1, '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '<h1 style=\"color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">CULTURAL AFFAIRS DIVISION (CAD)</h1><p style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">The Cultural Affairs Division (CAD) of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) Regional Office IX  Zamboanga Peninsula serves as the principal unit responsible for the preservation, promotion, and advancement of the cultural heritage, traditions, and identity of Muslim Filipinos within the region. Tasked with implementing the Commissions mandate under Republic Act No. 9997, the division ensures that the rich and diverse cultural expressions of Muslim communities are documented, safeguarded, and integrated into programs of education, community engagement, and development.</p><p style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">The divisions responsibilities include the planning, coordination, and implementation of cultural programs, projects, and activities that promote Islamic<br>practices, indigenous Muslim traditions, and other intangible and tangible forms of cultural heritage. It also facilitates research, documentation, and<br>dissemination of cultural knowledge to foster awareness, appreciation, and understanding among Muslim and non-Muslim populations alike.</p>', 'Cultural Affairs Division (CAD)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'cultural-affairs-division-cad', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:56:09', '2026-01-06 06:56:09', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?page_id=669', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(670, 1, '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '<h1>LEGAL AFFAIRS DIVISION (LAD)</h1>\n<br>\n<br>\n<p>The Legal Affairs Division (LAD) of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) Regional Office IX  Zamboanga Peninsula serves as the principal unit responsible for the provision of comprehensive legal services, advisory support, and policy guidance in the execution of the Commissions mandate under Republic Act No. 9997. The division ensures that all programs, projects, and operations of the regional office adhere strictly to existing laws, regulations, and established governance standards, thereby upholding the principles of legality, accountability, and integrity in public service.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>The divisions core responsibilities encompass the review, preparation, and monitoring of legal documents, contracts, memoranda, and agreements; provision of legal opinions and interpretations; and the development of internal policies and guidelines that strengthen the legal framework governing the operations of the regional office. Furthermore, LAD provides legal assistance to Muslim Filipinos in the region, particularly in matters relating to civil registry, family and personal status laws, property rights, inheritance, and other issues affecting the Muslim community.</p><p><br></p>\n<p>LAD also represents the regional office in legal proceedings, coordinates with national government agencies and local authorities on matters of law, and facilitates compliance with judicial and quasi-judicial requirements. The division plays a vital role in ensuring that the programs and initiatives of NCMF <br>Regional Office IX are implemented in full accordance with the law, while protecting the rights, interests, and welfare of Muslim communities in the Zamboanga Peninsula.</p>', 'Legal Affairs Division (LAD)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'legal-affairs-division-lad', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:55:28', '2026-01-06 06:55:28', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?page_id=670', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(671, 1, '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '<h1>PEACE BUILDING AND CONFLICT RESOLUTION DIVISION (PBCRD)</h1>\n<br><br>\n<p>The Peace Building and Conflict Resolution Division (PBCRD) of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos Regional Office IX serves as the primary institutional mechanism for advancing the Commissions mandate on fostering durable peace, social order, and harmonious relations within and among Muslim communities in the Zamboanga Peninsula. Guided by the national policy framework on peace, security, and development, the Division undertakes strategic interventions designed to prevent, mitigate, and resolve conflicts through culturally sensitive, rights-based, and community-centered approaches.</p><p><br></p>\n<p>The PBCRD exercises its function through the formulation and implementation of peace education initiatives, mediation and dialogue platforms, community engagement programs, and coordinated actions with national government agencies, local government units, civil society organizations, and traditional and <br>religious leaders. These undertakings aim to strengthen institutional capacities for conflict resolution, safeguard the welfare of Muslim Filipinos, and cultivate an environment conducive to mutual respect, inclusive governance, and sustainable peace.</p>', 'Peace Building and Conflict Resolution Division (PBCRD)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'peace-building-and-conflict-resolution-division-pbcrd', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:58:25', '2026-01-06 06:58:25', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?page_id=671', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(672, 1, '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '<h1>SETTLEMENT DIVISION (SD)</h1><br><br>\n<p>The Settlement Division of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos Regional Office IX (NCMF ZAMPEN) is responsible for the development, administration, and strengthening of Muslim Filipino settlement communities within the Zamboanga Peninsula. Anchored on the NCMFs mandate to promote the well-being, socio-economic upliftment, and cultural integrity of Muslim Filipinos, the Division implements programs aimed at ensuring equitable access to land, improving community governance, and fostering sustainable and dignified living conditions.</p><p><br></p>\n<p></p>\n<p>The Division undertakes a range of functions, including the facilitation of land-related documentation and verification processes, coordination of settlement planning and development initiatives, and the monitoring of community-based activities that reinforce self-governance and local participation. It extends technical assistance in the organization of settlement councils, promotes livelihood and capacity-building activities, and collaborates with partner agencies to address infrastructure, housing, and social service requirements. In pursuit of holistic community development, the Settlement Division actively engages with local government units, national government agencies, non government organizations, traditional leaders, and grassroots stakeholders.</p>', 'Settlement Division (SD)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'settlement-division-sd', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:52:17', '2026-01-06 06:52:17', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?page_id=672', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(673, 1, '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '2026-01-06 06:36:31', '<h1>SOCIO-ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT DIVISION (SEDD)</h1><br><br>\n<p>The Socio-Economic Development Division (SEDD) of NCMF Regional Office IX A  Zamboanga Peninsula is dedicated to empowering Muslim communities across the region through sustainable livelihood development, skills enhancement, and socio-economic upliftment programs. The division leads the implementation of projects that promote economic self-reliance, access to opportunities, and inclusive growth for Muslim Filipinos.</p><p><br></p>\n<p>SEDD supports the development, promotion, and protection of the Halal industry by ensuring that community-based economic programs align with Halal principles and standards. It likewise leads the implementation of Halal-related socio-economic initiatives in the region, including capability-building sessions, <br>awareness activities, and support to Halal-compliant enterprises and livelihood programs. The division also works closely with Halal Certifying Bodies, national government agencies, local government units, cooperatives, and Muslim organizations to strengthen the Halal ecosystem and expand market opportunities for Muslim Filipinos.</p>\n<p>Guided by the mandate of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos, SEDD IXA continues to champion programs that improve quality of life, strengthen <br>local economies, and uphold the welfare and dignity of Muslim communities in Zamboanga Peninsula.</p>', 'Socio-Economic Development Division (SEDD)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'socio-economic-development-division-sedd', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:54:08', '2026-01-06 06:54:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?page_id=673', 0, 'page', '', 0),
