(725, 1, '2026-01-06 06:51:54', '2026-01-06 06:51:54', '<h1>SETTLEMENT DIVISION (SD)</h1><p>The Settlement Division of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos Regional Office IX (NCMF ZAMPEN) is responsible for the development, administration, and strengthening of Muslim Filipino settlement communities within the Zamboanga Peninsula. Anchored on the NCMFs mandate to promote the well-being, socio-economic upliftment, and cultural integrity of Muslim Filipinos, the Division implements programs aimed at ensuring equitable access to land, improving community governance, and fostering sustainable and dignified living conditions.</p><p></p><p>The Division undertakes a range of functions, including the facilitation of land-related documentation and verification processes, coordination of settlement <br />planning and development initiatives, and the monitoring of community-based activities that reinforce self-governance and local participation. It extends technical assistance in the organization of settlement councils, promotes livelihood and capacity-building activities, and collaborates with partner agencies to address infrastructure, housing, and social service requirements. In pursuit of holistic community development, the Settlement Division actively engages with local government units, national government agencies, non government organizations, traditional leaders, and grassroots stakeholders.</p>', 'Settlement Division (SD)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '672-revision-v1', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:51:54', '2026-01-06 06:51:54', '', 672, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?p=725', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
