(740, 1, '2026-01-06 06:56:09', '2026-01-06 06:56:09', '<h1 style=\"color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">CULTURAL AFFAIRS DIVISION (CAD)</h1><p style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">The Cultural Affairs Division (CAD) of the National Commission on Muslim Filipinos (NCMF) Regional Office IX  Zamboanga Peninsula serves as the principal unit responsible for the preservation, promotion, and advancement of the cultural heritage, traditions, and identity of Muslim Filipinos within the region. Tasked with implementing the Commissions mandate under Republic Act No. 9997, the division ensures that the rich and diverse cultural expressions of Muslim communities are documented, safeguarded, and integrated into programs of education, community engagement, and development.</p><p style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">&nbsp;</p><p style=\"font-size: 16px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26);\">The divisions responsibilities include the planning, coordination, and implementation of cultural programs, projects, and activities that promote Islamic<br>practices, indigenous Muslim traditions, and other intangible and tangible forms of cultural heritage. It also facilitates research, documentation, and<br>dissemination of cultural knowledge to foster awareness, appreciation, and understanding among Muslim and non-Muslim populations alike.</p>', 'Cultural Affairs Division (CAD)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '669-revision-v1', '', '', '2026-01-06 06:56:09', '2026-01-06 06:56:09', '', 669, 'http://localhost/ncmf-ro9/?p=740', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
